ONE NIGHT STAND
by Giannis G. Georgiou

The first adventure of Sandy Owens.

Type 'help' for user interface tips and 'about' for credits. Enjoy!

You wake up in a half lit room, early in the morning, with a horrible hangover. "I'll never drink vodka again," you think. Yet, you know you are probably lying. Wait a minute. Where are you? What happened last night? And why are you completely naked? You look around looking for clues.

And here is a big one: on the room's single and only bed, you can see an equally naked dude, sleeping face down.

Okay. So, you've probably slept with this dude. Not that you recall anything from last night. You assess the situation, while looking around for your clothes. You first find your heels. "That's a start," you think, putting them on.

A student's bedroom

This must be a university student's room: small, cheap, messy, and stuffy. Pheww! You don't like students, much. Yet, here you are, waking up next to one. What is the matter with you, girl!

Your dress is partially visible, squashed under your date's bulky body. Poor thing... Near the bed, you see a cheap bedside lamp. The lamp's shade is covered with a red shirt.

Pushed against one wall, you see a narrow closet. Next to it, there is a desk with only one drawer.

A cat wanders around the room.

You can go west or south.
> x shirt

> x shirt

Someone has covered the lamp's shade with a red shirt; to add to the room's atmosphere, perhaps? You thank the universe for not having caught fire! That would have been some night!

(Considering, also, the vodka that runs in your blood, you would not have stood a chance!)
> take shirt

> take shirt

The red shirt is hot. Literally. You pick it up and put it in your inventory. You are naked, though, so you can't exactly define the term 'inventory.'

Anyway.
> wear shirt

> wear shirt

You put the red shirt on. The dude's physique is large enough for it to cover your nakedness, although some would still call you provocative.
> open drawer

> open drawer

Being as silent as you can, you open the drawer.

It contains some one-night stand memorabilia.
> x stand

> x stand

The drawer is stuffed with one-night stand souvenirs. Mostly lots of women's underwear. Plus one vibrator, one unused prophylactic, one soiled... Just to name a few.

Hey! Wait a minute! Your panties are in here, too! That sly bastard has snatched your underwear, to have a story to tell his grandchildren...
> take panties

> take panties

You take the tiny thing.
> x panties

> x panties

Your poor little piece of underwear. It is a cute black laced pair of panties. Too bad that it has been in that drawer with all the other stuff. It needs washing.
> wear panties

> wear panties

Nah, you're not going to wear dirty underwear.
> x women's underwear

> x women's underwear

Several pairs of panties and a few thongs.
And one bra, too.
> x bra

> x bra

It is a brown, old fashioned piece of lingerie from the '50s. No, you're joking. But it does look ancient.
> x vibrator

> x vibrator

Remember when you used to have one of these toys? You threw it away when your mum came to visit. Then, you replaced it with anonymous men. What a life...
> x unused

> x unused

A new prophylactic, sealed in its little envelope. Expiry date, still valid.
> x soiled

> x soiled

Could it be the one he used with you? Probably not. This one looks ancient.
> x dress

> x dress

Your elegant blue dress. Short, but not slutty. Classy, but not snotty. You silently congratulate yourself for your taste.

Then, one look at the guy sleeping on it is enough to make you change your mind.
> take dress

> take dress

You gently pull one end of your dress. Then, you yank it harder.
The dude twists a little and, without opening his eyes, he says: "Oh, Sandy, please. Let me sleep some more, honey."

Sandy? The boy remembers your name! How sweet!

Then, you realise that you don't recall his. "Oh, come on," you say to yourself. "This can't be that hard..." Gosh, what is this guy's name? At first, it feels like a little game; like a puzzle: you squeeze your brains to remember what you know about this guy. How would Sherlock Holmes solve this? "Let's retrace our steps," you think. An image of him leaning towards you in a night club... His words: "Hi, I am... My name is... My friends call me..."

No. It's futile. You don't remember the name. Dammit!

It's not a game anymore. You are starting to feel bad about this. This young dude probably had the night of his life with you. He worshipped you. He honoured you. If he were awake, he would probably offer to bring you breakfast in bed. But you... You don't even remember his name. What kind of cynical bitch are you?

Oh my! It is true. You have turned into a serial sex machine. You have been wasting yourself, from one night stand to one night stand, from coctail party to orgy, without a single clue about whom you share this experiences with. You have been consumming men like nachos, not giving a second thought about their feelings.

Nor about yours! That's right! You have feelings, too! And you have been suppressing them, because of some twisted self image, which pushes you towards numb and quickly consummated relationships.

No more! This is a turning point! You take a deep breath and decide something very important (or so you think): You HAVE to remember this guy's name. You will make it your quest, finding out this guy's name. There is no way you leave the house before addressing him with his name. You will treat this boy with respect. And then, you will change your life.

You give the dude an awkward caress on the head, with an oblique "Shhh." He changes side and continues sleeping.
> s

> s

Phew! The corridor smells even stuffier than that dude's bedroom! What's wrong with them students?

A corridor

The flat's short and narrow corridor connects the two bedrooms with the living space, to the east. A doorless opening to the south leads to a small bathroom. (Doorless! Wow!)

To the west, there is the door to Mara's room. Although you don't recall much from last night, you have a vague knowledge of Mara being the other tenant in the flat.

You can go north, east or south.
> x door

> x door

This is Mara's room.
Then, you ask yourself how come you remember HER name and not HIS!
The door is painted pink. You never liked pink.
> s

> s

As you step inside the cold bathroom, you wonder how anyone can use the toilet without a door. Then, you see a semi-transparent shower curtain hanging by the opening, to be used as a room devider. Right.

A bathroom

The blue-tiled bathroom features a sink, a toilet seat and a shower without a curtain. Of course. On the floor, you can see a half-empty bottle of chlorine solution. Above the sink hangs a mirror cabinet.

You can go north.
> x bottle

> x bottle

The bottle contains a powerful chemical. "Keep away from eyes, hair, skin, and clothes," says the label. "Do not drink. Do not bath in it. Do not give as present to little kids." All that jazz.
> take bottle

> take bottle

You never know when some good old chlorine solution may come in handy.
> x sink

> x sink

What are you sinking about?

Aaahh... A good old German joke your father used to say.
> x toilet

> x toilet

The toilet seat looks clean. Weird.
> x shower

> x shower

Withoug a curtain, Norman Bates can't surprise you in the shower. You also can't keep the water from spraying all over the room. There are several shampoos and shower gels, as well as a soap bar. You wouldn't go near the soap bar, though; you think you can see some dude's hair on it.
> x soap

> x soap

Bubbly things. Someone enjoys variety of scents. The soap bar has some hair stuck to it.
> x hair

> x hair

The soap has someone's hair stuck to it. You take your magnifying glass and inspect it. The hair belongs to the human race. Male's, probably. Body hair. Not sure which part. Sure that you don't want to figure it out.

You leave the hair where it is.
> x cabinet

> x cabinet

You admire yourself in the mirror for a moment. Then, you continue with your quest.
> open cabinet

> open cabinet

You open it. You say goodbye to your reflection, as it gives its place to the cabinet's contents.

It contains a mouth guard and a cup with about a dozen of toothbrushes.
> x mouth guard

> x mouth guard

A plastic mouth guard, for the sufferers of bruxism. You are not one of them.
> x cup

> x cup

You wonder if the toothbrushes belong to different women who have slept with that guy...
> close cabinet

> close cabinet

You close the cabinet. It's one of these moments, in horror films, when the heroine closes the mirror cabinet, only to see the killer's reflection behind her.

No, there's just you. It's nice to see your face, again.
> use toilet

> use toilet

You sit on the toilet seat and relax your lower muscles. Then, all of a sudden, you jolt up, turn around and... throw up. Yuck.

You flush and try to forget about it, even though the sour aftertaste works hard to refresh your memory.
> use shower

> use shower

With quick moves, you take the shirt off and hop into the shower. You turn the water on, while singing the theme from Psycho's shower sequence -remixed with a pinch of the theme from Friday the 13th.

Unfortunately, the water is icy cold.
Your teeth rattle. Maybe that mouthguard wasn't such a bad idea, after all.

Okay, that's enough. You get out of the shower and dry yourself with the first towel you lay your hands on. Still shaking, you put the red shirt back on.
> n

> n

A corridor

The flat's short and narrow corridor connects the two bedrooms with the living space, to the east. A doorless opening to the south leads to a small bathroom.

To the west, there is the door to Mara's room.

You can go north, east or south.
> e

> e

A kitchen & living room

A tiny living space serving as living room, front door hall and kitchen. The aesthetics? Unacceptable. The architecture? Non existent.

The living space's furniture is quite poor and basic. A second (or thirtieth) hand couch slouches between a plywood bookcase and an IKEA coffee table.

The kitchen is equipped with most of the essentials, but the grease on the floor tells you that you wouldn't want to approach that part of the house.

A telescope sits on its tripod, pointing outside the window. The front door is unlocked, waiting for you, when you're ready.

You can go west.
> x telescope

> x telescope

You wonder about the purpose of this powerful telescope. Astronomy or voyeurism?
Let's see... It's pointing out of the window, but not towards the sky. Hmm...
> use telescope

> use telescope

You point the telescope, from the kitchen & living room, to a flat across the street.
You spot an old couple finding that old flare among dirty dishes. Hmm.
> take telescope

> take telescope

You leave the tripod and take just the telescope.
> x couch

> x couch

It looks comfortable, but you really have no time for couch surfing.
> x bookcase

> x bookcase

Lots of interesting books, mostly about... roleplaying games? Wow, kinky! You remember your ex-ex-ex-boyfriend, who was very much into roleplaying. Where is that nurse costume, by the way...?

Oh, wait. You only see dragons and wizards, here. And these costumes look expensive.

No. You don't get it. Anyway. You leave the books where they are.
> x table

> x table

You look under the coffee table. No. The dude's name is not written here.
> x tripod

> x tripod

You remember that guy whose nickname was 'the tripod' -and not because he was a stable character. You lost touch with him after he got into porn.
> x door

> x door

The door is closed, but under it there is enough space for any rodent to crawl in. Yes, even capybaras.
> x grease

> x grease

A slimey substance that covers the whole kitchen floor, looking almost as if it's breathing. You are not sure that your heels are high enough to walk on this kitchen swamp.
> use bottle on grease

> use bottle on grease

You pour some chlorine on the greasy floor. Some of the grease gives in, but nothing major happens. Wow! You haven't seen anything that dirty before!
