You walk outside, on a balcony overlooking a cosy neighbourhood. You try to guess how many university students hooked up with each other last night. Naah. University students bore you. Boy, you must have been really drunk to hook up with one of them, yourself.

A balcony

The neighbourhood is quiet, being a Sunday morning.  There is a window with the curtains open. If you are a little careful, you can see inside the room, without being noticed.

You can go east.
> x window

> x window

You take a peek inside the room. You see Mara. Although you don't recall much from last night, you have a vague knowledge of Mara being the other tenant in the flat.

Then, you ask yourself how come you remember HER name and not HIS!

She is sat at her desk, with her back turned to you.

Stuck on the wall, you see a photograph. You can't really tell who is in it. On another wall, you see the poster of a pop band. Yikes. On a shelf, there is a metallic figurine.
> x Mara

> x Mara

Mara is a medium built brunette in her early twenties.
She is currently sitting at her desk, with her back turned to you.
> x photo

> x photo

The photograph is stuck onto the wall, across the room, opposite you. It is too far to tell who is in it. Not that you would necessarily know them.
> x poster

> x poster

Some boy band you don't want to know about.
> x figurine

> x figurine

A small figurine made of silver-coloured metal. Is it a trophy of some sort? Who knows.
> use telescope on photo

> use telescope on photo

Using the telescope, you are actually able to see some faces on the photograph! You see several dudes and... Aha. You recognise the dude next door, as well as Mara. They are hugging very lovingly.

It seems that Mara and the dude next door have something going -or at least had something going, some time ago.
> i

> i

You are carrying your high heels, a red shirt, your panties, a bottle of chlorine solution, a telescope and a vivid mental image of Mara and the dude hugging.
> x image

> x image

You have a very vivid mental image of Mara and the dude hugging. The thought that -even if drunk- you have shared the same man with Mara makes you uncomfortable.
> use telescope on poster

> use telescope on poster

You turn the telescope towards the boy band poster. Look at those guys' hair! You see a signed autograph on one corner. "To Mara, for a night of unbearable pleasure. -The Shrimps"
> use telescope on figurine

> use telescope on figurine

You point the telescope at the figurine lying on Mara's shelf. It is the statuette of a man slouching in front of a computer. An inscription says "2014 - Best Text Adventure: The Sore Foot, by Mara Stuart."
