> knock door

> knock door

Mara opens the door with a sour face.
She seems not too keen to talk with you, although you don't really know why. "What do you want?" she asks.
"Hi Mara. You must be... the flatmate. Err... Your flatmate told me so much about you."
"So?" she asks, unimpressed.

An awkward pause.

"Listen. Something really funny happened to me... I was pretty drunk last night and I can't seem to... remember his name," you smile.
"And?"
"Can you tell me his name, please?"
"No."
"Why?" you ask.
"Because I don't like you."

At least, you can appreciate her straightforwardness.

"That was fast," you protest. "You've only been listening to me for 30 seconds."
"30 seconds and 3 hours of moaning. Last night."

Oh.

"So, I know you quite well, enough to say that you and I are not going to be excellent friends," she scowls. "Now, get out of here."

She shuts the door in your face.
