> knock door

> knock door

Mara opens the door with a sour face.
"What is it, now?" she asks.

"About you and your flatmate... Did you two date or something?" you ask her.
"What? Where did you get that idea?"
"I don't know," you say, "I think from the way you protect his private data."

Mara takes a good look at you. "And what if we did?"
"Oh, nothing. I mean... What happened between him and me last night was very casual. I really wouldn't want to stand between you two guys..."

Mara seems to be trying to act cool, although the subject is obviously touchy.

"This is all ancient history for me. In fact..." She ponders for a second. "You know what? I'll make a deal with you. I have reasons to believe that my flatmate has taken something from me; something personal. And he won't give it back. You go find that for me and I'll give you some information on the subject that is bothering you."
"You'll tell me his name?" you ask enthusiastically.
"Well. Maybe."

"So, what's the item I'm looking for?"
"Oh, you figure it out yourself! I don't like you THAT much! Now, scram!"

She closes the door in your face.
